myVlanMIB.name: myVlanMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

myVlanMIB.description: This module defines my vlan mibs.

VlanList.name: VlanList
VlanList.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight vlans, with the first octet specifying vlans 1 through 8, the second octet specifying vlans 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered vlan, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered vlan. Thus, each vlan of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1', then that vlan is included in the set of vlans; the vlan is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

myVlanMaxNumber.name: myVlanMaxNumber
myVlanMaxNumber.description: Number of MAX vlans this system supported.

myVlanCurrentNumber.name: myVlanCurrentNumber
myVlanCurrentNumber.description: Number of current vlans this system have.

mySystemMaxVID.name: mySystemMaxVID
mySystemMaxVID.description: Max vlans of VID this system supported.

myVlanIfConfigEntry.name: myVlanIfConfigEntry
myVlanIfConfigEntry.description: list of vlan and it's port group table.

myVlanIfAccessVlan.name: myVlanIfAccessVlan
myVlanIfAccessVlan.description: The value indicate the VID of the vlan which that this port belong to. This field is effective for only access port.

myVlanIfNativeVlan.name: myVlanIfNativeVlan
myVlanIfNativeVlan.description: The value indicate the VID of the native vlan of that this port . This field is effective for only trunk port.

myVlanIfAllowedVlanList.name: myVlanIfAllowedVlanList
myVlanIfAllowedVlanList.description: Each bit in every octet in octet string assigned to a vlan, the value of the bit indicates that if the vlan is belong to allowed vlan list of this interface. It indicates that assigned vlan is member of allowed vlan list of this interface if value of the bit is 1. The lowest bit of first byte correspond to vlan 1 and the lowest bit of second byte correspond to vlan 9 vlan. This field is effective for only trunk port.

myVlanEntry.name: myVlanEntry
myVlanEntry.description: list of vlan and it's distribution table.

myVlanPortMemberAction.name: myVlanPortMemberAction
myVlanPortMemberAction.description: Each octet in member map assigned to a physical port, the value of the octect indicates the action of a physical port in the vlan. Drop(1) indicate that the vlan doesn't include this physical port, Add(2) indicate that the vlan include this physical port.

myVlanApMemberAction.name: myVlanApMemberAction
myVlanApMemberAction.description: Each octet in member map assigned to a aggreate port, the value of the octect indicates the action of a aggreate port in the vlan. Drop(1) indicate that the vlan doesn't include this physical port, Add(2) indicate that the vlan include this physical port.

myVlanEntryStatus.name: myVlanEntryStatus
myVlanEntryStatus.description: Status of this entry, set this object to valid will creat a vlan of this entry, and set its value to invalid will delete the vlan of this entry.

myVlanPortConfigMode.name: myVlanPortConfigMode
myVlanPortConfigMode.description: Port mode, indicates that port is an access(1), trunk(2), dot1q-tunnel(3), hybrid(4), other(5), uplink(6), host(7) or promiscuous(8) port.

myVlanPortAccessVlan.name: myVlanPortAccessVlan
myVlanPortAccessVlan.description: The value indicate the VID of the vlan which that this port belong to. This field is effective for only access port.

myVlanPortNativeVlan.name: myVlanPortNativeVlan
myVlanPortNativeVlan.description: The value indicate the VID of the native vlan of that this port . This field is effective for only trunk,hybrid,uplink and dot1q_tunnel port.

myVlanPortAllowedVlanList.name: myVlanPortAllowedVlanList
myVlanPortAllowedVlanList.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight vlans, with the first octet specifying vlans 0 through 7, the second octet specifying vlans 8 through 15, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered vlan, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered vlan. Thus, each vlan of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1', then that vlan is included in the set of vlans; the vlan is not included if its bit has a value of '0'

myVlanConfigEntry.name: myVlanConfigEntry
myVlanConfigEntry.description: list of vlan and it's distribution table.

myVlanConfigAction.name: myVlanConfigAction
myVlanConfigAction.description: The value 1 to create a vlan, 0 to delete a vlan.

myVlanConfigPortMember.name: myVlanConfigPortMember
myVlanConfigPortMember.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1', then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

myVlanMIBCompliance.name: myVlanMIBCompliance
myVlanMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the My Vlan MIB

myVlanMIBGroup.name: myVlanMIBGroup
myVlanMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects providing vlan configure .
